    "body": "@steveklabnik I mentioned the wiki system as an alternative because being able to fix or improve the documentation in place is very attractive. This has worked really good for e.g. `cppreference.com`.\n\nThe main drawback of the wiki system is that dealing with spammers and reverting bad modifications takes a _huge_ amount of time. For cmake, vtk, and many others the wiki system hasn't worked out at all. \n\nI am not in favor of a wiki system either.\n",
